/target

# === Chainlink managed ===
# .chainlink/ — local-only tracker state (no remote sync by design).
# SQLite store + WAL are per-machine; rules/ is project policy and
# should be tracked so collaborators share workflow config.
.chainlink/issues.db
.chainlink/issues.db-wal
.chainlink/issues.db-shm
.chainlink/session.json
.chainlink/.active-issue

# .chainlink/ — DO track these (project-level policy):
#   .chainlink/rules/             — project coding standards

# === Legacy crosslink leftovers (post-migration) ===
# Pre-migration tracker state lives in .crosslink.archive/ (read-only;
# do not modify — see docs/tracker-history.md). The .crosslink/ entry
# remains defensively in case crosslink tooling is re-run against this
# repo and re-creates the directory.
.crosslink/
.crosslink.archive/

# .claude/ — auto-generated hooks, not project source
.claude/hooks/
.claude/commands/
.claude/mcp/

# .claude/ — DO track these (if manually configured):
#   .claude/settings.json         — Claude Code project settings
#   .claude/settings.local.json is per-developer, ignore separately if needed
# Chainlink runtime artifacts (rules/ tracked, runtime state excluded)
.chainlink/daemon.log
.chainlink/daemon.pid

# === Internal-notes docs untracked post-v1.1 ===
# Both files were committed up through the v1.1.0 tag (which keeps the
# historical snapshots for anyone checking out v1.1.0 or earlier).
# Going forward they live as private working notes; future edits stay
# off the wire. To re-track, remove the entries below and `git add` the
# file.
RETROSPECTIVE.md
